strong>Key Responsibilities<\/strong><\/h2><ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li> Research &amp; Analysis \u2013 Conduct critical research on political theories of AI governance, regulatory frameworks, and ethical challenges.<\/li>\n\n<li> Literature Review \u2013 Analyze academic and policy literature, identifying gaps in existing discussions on AI governance.<\/li>\n\n<li>Policy &amp; Legal Assessment \u2013 Evaluate AI-related policies, legislation, and governance models at national and global levels, focusing on their implications for democracy and social structures.<\/li>\n\n<li>Ethical &amp; Philosophical Inquiry \u2013 Examine AI through the lens of justice, fairness, accountability, transparency, and fundamental rights. <\/li>\n\n<li>Collaboration &amp; Interdisciplinary Engagement \u2013 Work closely with legal experts, technologists, and social scientists to develop a well-rounded understanding of AI\u2019s impact on governance and political systems.<\/li><\/ul><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Who Should Apply?<\/strong><\/h2><p>We are looking for candidates with:<\/p><ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li> A postgraduate or equivalent advanced degree in Political Science, Political Theory, Public Policy, Philosophy, or a related field.<\/li>\n\n<li> Strong research and analytical skills, with the ability to critically assess policy documents, academic literature, and legal texts<\/li>\n\n<li> Expertise in political theory and public policy, with a focus on technology ethics, digital governance, or AI regulation.<\/li>\n\n<li> Excellent written and verbal communication skills to articulate complex ideas to academic, policy, and public audiences.<\/li>\n\n<li> Experience in interdisciplinary research or collaboration on policy, technology, or legal studies is a plus.<\/li><\/ul><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Benefits<\/strong><\/h2><ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>A dynamic research environment at a leading institute.<\/li>\n\n<li> Opportunity to think together and contribute to emerging debates on AI, governance, and democracy.<\/li>\n\n<li> Potential for contract extension, depending on research progress and funding availability.<\/li>\n\n<li>Salary: \u20b937,000 per month.<\/li><\/ul><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How to Apply<\/strong><\/h2><p>Interested candidates can send their CV, cover letter, and relevant work samples to this <a href=\"rubina@iiitd.ac.in\">E-mail<\/a>.<\/p><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/iiitd.ac.in\/sites\/default\/files\/docs\/positions\/2025\/Research%20Associate%20%E2%80%93%20Political%20Theory%20of%20AI.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to view th<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/iiitd.ac.in\/sites\/default\/files\/docs\/positions\/2025\/Research%20Associate%20%E2%80%93%20Political%20Theory%20of%20AI.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">e official notification of the post of research ass<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/iiitd.ac.in\/sites\/default\/files\/docs\/positions\/2025\/Research%20Associate%20%E2%80%93%20Political%20Theory%20of%20AI.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ociate at IIIT Delhi.<\/a><\/strong><\/h4><div data-wp-interactive=\"core\/file\" class=\"wp-block-file aligncenter\"><object data-wp-bind--hidden=\"!state.hasPdfPreview\" hidden class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"https:\/\/cse.noticebard.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/23\/2025\/03\/Research-Associate-\u2013-Political-Theory-of-AI.pdf\" type=\"application\/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Embed of Click here to view the Brochure..\"><\/object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-050cdcd4-7a9a-4243-9b9e-09660360e4c2\" href=\"https:\/\/cse.noticebard.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/23\/2025\/03\/Research-Associate-\u2013-Political-Theory-of-AI.pdf\">Click here to view the Brochure.<\/a><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Applications are invited for the post of research associate at IIIT Delhi. Apply by March 27. About IIIT Delh